                     <interp inst="def1-2448-18481023" type="surname" value="PARSONS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2448-18481023" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">THOMAS PARSONS</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18481023-2448-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18481023-2448-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18481023-2448-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp>, stealing 19lbs. weight of pot-metal, and 1 metal waste, value 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; the goods of <persName id="t18481023-name-1211" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1211" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1211" type="surname" value="PONTIFEX"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1211" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18481023-2448-offence-1 t18481023-name-1211"></join>William Pontifex</persName> and another, his masters.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18481023-name-1212" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1212" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1212" type="surname" value="SHARP"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1212" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN SHARP</persName>
                  </hi>. I am manager to William and Edward Pontifex, copper-smiths and engineers. The prisoner has been in their employ about fourteen years—on the evening of 13th Oct. I saw him leaving the premises, and I kept him in conversation to point him out to the officer—I have seen the metal produced—it is called pot-metal—I have no doubt it is the property of Messrs. Pontifex—I can swear to this article, it is a rough casting—it is never sold or sent out in the state it is now in.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184810230203"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CLARKSON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What is it called? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Waste—it is part of a washer and waste—it is made to fix in a washer—I cannot say that I had seen this on the premises.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18481023-name-1213" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1213" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1213" type="surname" value="BURTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1213" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES BURTON</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman M</hi> 272). I watched the prisoner—I saw him come out of the factory—I took him in a passage in Gravel-lane, Southwark, at the back of a marine-store dealer's shop—I told him I suspected he had got some property he had brought from his employers'—he said, "It is a bad job, it is the first lot I brought from my employers"—I found this metal on him, some in his hat, and some in different pockets.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
